  <id>page.codeberg.JakobDev.jdReplace</id>
  <name>jdReplace</name>
  <summary>With jdReplace you can replace a text in all files of a directory</summary>
  <developer id="page.codeberg.jakobdev">
    <name>JakobDev</name>
  </developer>
  <metadata_license>CC0-1.0</metadata_license>
  <project_license>GPL-3.0-only</project_license>
  <description>
    <p>jdReplace is a simple mass search and replace tool. You set a directory, a text to replace, the replacement and click OK. jdReplace will do the rest.</p>
  </description>
